# Phase 3: Design System
# Agent: web-engineer

# Generate design tokens from brand brief
import "libraries/design-tokens.flow"

# Build base components
let component_list = "Button,Card,Section,Badge,NavBar,Footer,PricingCard,TestimonialCard,FeatureCard,IntegrationLogo,CTABanner,FAQAccordion"

foreach component in "${component_list}"
  import "libraries/component.flow"
end

# Build layout primitives
prompt: You are a web engineer. Read the project in the current directory. Create layout components: a Container component (max-width, padding, centering), a Grid component (responsive CSS grid wrapper), and a Stack component (vertical/horizontal flex with gap). Use the design tokens already configured. Place them in the components directory following the project's conventions.

# Design system review
review max 1
  prompt: You are a web engineer. Review all components created so far for design consistency. Check that they all use the design tokens (not hardcoded colors/spacing), follow the same naming convention, and have consistent prop patterns. Fix any inconsistencies directly.
end

# Verify it still builds
retry max 2
  run: npm run build 2>&1 || true
  if command_failed
    prompt: The build failed after creating design system components. Read the error output in ${last_stderr} and fix the issues. Common problems are import errors, missing dependencies, or TypeScript issues.
  end
end
